{
  "stem": "15943.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 25.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But then when she was going out of the ghetto, she go-- right before it became the ghetto, she-- one day, she says, I'm going to come and knock down the tree.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I don't want the Jews to have the pleasure of the tree.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Those were her people she lived with.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And my grandmother was her best friend.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My mother was her daughter's best friend.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I was a child with this family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now here she was going to knock down the tree because the Jews shouldn't enjoy it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I remember my mother getting very angry.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "She said, you, you ruined our lives.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I don't remember the wording exactly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I have it written down in the book.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "You could take your tree.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It so happened that the ghetto was closed up, and she could never knock down the tree.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And despite her, the tree stayed there until we knocked it down for firewood because we needed, we needed wood.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Harry-- ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Harry ?] was brainwashed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "He was 13 years old, grew up with us, spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "He loved Jewish history, loved-- he used to say that he's going to marry me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And I said, no,  you can't marry me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "You're not a Jew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I knew he wasn't a Jew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Big deal.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "So I convert and become a Jew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "There was nothing to it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And when they moved out of the area that became the ghetto, he came back only three months later, and he was dressed in the brown uniform of the Hitler Youth.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He looked like a poster boy for, for Hitler's advertisement because he had blue eyes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had blond hair.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had a nightstick in his hand.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he repeated the same ugly words what we heard on the radio.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Jews are parasites.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
